<section xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>37-201.08</num>
  <heading>Commodities sold by weight; “ton” defined.</heading>
  <text>When any commodity is sold by weight it shall be net weight. When any commodity is sold by the ton, it shall be understood to mean 2,000 pounds avoirdupois.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">Mar. 3, 1921, 41 Stat. 1219, ch. 118, § 8</annotation>
    <annotation type="History">Mar. 31, 1945, 59 Stat. 45, ch. 46, § 1</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 10-109.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 10-108.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
